---

## 🇵🇹 Portugal National Team – Season Report

### 🏆 Major Achievement: UEFA Nations League Champions
Portugal won their **second UEFA Nations League title** in June 2025:
- **Quarterfinals:** Beat Denmark (1-0 away, 5-2 home)
- **Semifinals:** Lost 1-2 to Germany (June 4)
- **Final (June 8):** Drew 2-2 with Spain, won **5-3 on penalties** to claim the trophy

### 🏅 UEFA Euro 2024
Portugal reached the **quarterfinals**:
- Group stage: Beat Czechia (2-1) and Turkey (3-0), lost to Georgia (0-2)
- Round of 16: 0-0 draw vs Slovenia, won 3-0 on penalties
- **Knocked out in quarterfinals** (lost on penalties to France)

### 🌍 FIFA World Cup 2026 Qualifying
Portugal **topped Group F** to qualify directly for the World Cup:
- **Record:** 5 wins, 1 draw, 0 losses (exceptional form)
- **Key results:**
  - 5-0 win vs Armenia (away)
  - 9-1 win vs Armenia (home) – biggest win of the campaign
  - 3-2 win vs Hungary (away)
- Only dropped points: 2-2 draw vs Hungary

### 📊 Overall Verdict
| Competition | Result |
|---|---|
| UEFA Euro 2024 | Quarterfinals |
| UEFA Nations League | **Champions** 🏆 |
| World Cup 2026 Qualifying | Qualified as group winners |
| World Cup 2026 (so far) | 1 draw, 1 win (5-0 vs Uzbekistan) |

**Head Coach:** Roberto Martínez (since Jan 2023)  
**Star performer:** Cristiano Ronaldo (scored twice in World Cup opener vs Uzbekistan)

**Bottom line:** A very strong season — silverware in the Nations League, solid qualifying campaign, and competitive at the Euros. Portugal looks well-set for the 2026 World Cup.

