2026-06-24 20:17:53.881 [http-nio-8080-exec-2] INFO  com.chatbot.aspect.LoggingAspect - ║  OUTPUT: Here is a comprehensive report on Portugal for the **2026 FIFA World Cup**.

### 1. Qualification Status
- **Result:** Qualified ✅ (Won Group F in UEFA qualifying)
- **Record:** 4 wins, 1 draw, 1 loss

### 2. Head Coach & Captain
- **Coach:** Roberto Martínez (Spain)
- **Captain:** Cristiano Ronaldo

### 3. Key Squad Breakdown (Current Core)

**Goalkeepers:**
- Diogo Costa (FC Porto) – *Likely starter*
- José Sá (Wolves), Rui Silva (Sporting CP)

**Defenders:**
- Rúben Dias (Man City) – *Anchor*
- João Cancelo (Barcelona), Diogo Dalot (Man Utd)
- Nuno Mendes (PSG), Gonçalo Inácio (Sporting)
- *Young talents:* António Silva (Benfica), Tomás Araújo (Benfica)

**Midfielders:**
- Bruno Fernandes (Man Utd) – *Creative engine*
- Bernardo Silva (Man City) – *Technical leader*
- João Neves (PSG) – *Rising star*
- João Palhinha (Bayern Munich) – *Defensive shield*
- Vitinha (PSG), Rúben Neves (Al Hilal)

**Forwards:**
- Cristiano Ronaldo (Al Nassr) – *Captain & all-time top scorer*
- Rafael Leão (AC Milan) – *Key winger*
- Gonçalo Ramos (PSG) – *Striker*
- João Félix (Al Nassr), Pedro Neto (Chelsea)
- Francisco Conceição (Juventus) – *Pacey dribbler*

### 4. Strengths
- **Depth:** Strong options in midfield and attack.
- **Experience:** Core players have won Euro 2016 and Nations League.
- **Defensive spine:** Rúben Dias + Diogo Costa is world-class.
- **Versatility:** Tactical flexibility under Martínez (4-3-3 / 3-4-3).

### 5. Weaknesses / Concerns
- **Age of Ronaldo:** At 41 in 2026, reliance on him may limit pressing.
- **Left-back depth:** Nuno Mendes injury-prone; few alternatives.
- **Aerial vulnerability:** Against tall, physical sides.
- **Big-game mentality:** Recent quarterfinal exits (2022 WC, Euro 2024).

### 6. Prediction
- **Group Stage:** Expected to advance comfortably.
- **Knockout potential:** Quarterfinal or Semifinal ceiling.
- **X-factor:** João Neves & Rafael Leão could break through as tournament stars.

